      {
        "id": "claim.repo_identity",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "Rudel is a Bun/Turborepo TypeScript monorepo for ingesting Claude Code session transcripts, storing them in ClickHouse, and presenting analytics such as token usage, session duration, activity patterns, model usage, and related dashboard views.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "about": "component.repository",
        "code_anchors": [
          {
            "file": "README.md"
          },
          {
            "file": "CLAUDE.md"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "claim.monorepo_boundaries",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "The repo is organized around apps/api for the Bun HTTP API, apps/cli for the published rudel CLI, apps/web for the Vite React dashboard, packages/api-routes for the shared oRPC/Zod contract, packages/ch-schema for ClickHouse schema and generated ingest helpers, and packages/sql-schema for Drizzle/Postgres auth tables.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "about": "component.repository",
        "code_anchors": [
          {
            "file": "CONTRIBUTING.md"
          },
          {
            "file": "CLAUDE.md"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "claim.local_setup_commands",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "Local standalone setup uses Bun 1.3+, Docker or OrbStack, `bun install`, and `bun run dev:local`; that script starts Postgres and ClickHouse containers, runs migrations, and launches the API on localhost:4010 plus the web app on localhost:4011. The full verification command is `bun run verify`.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "about": "flow.local_development",
        "code_anchors": [
